---

For ME 12 through 16.1 this branch is functionally identical to main. Every confirmed HAP offset is the same. If you are on an 8th–13th gen platform either branch will do the same thing.

The difference is ME 18 (Meteor Lake). Main skips the write and exits cleanly. This branch does the same — but also dumps the IOE Soft Straps region so you can share the data and help confirm the offset.

---

## Why ME 18 is not confirmed yet

Meteor Lake dropped the discrete PCH. The descriptor layout changed completely — no PCH Straps at `0x100`. HAP is almost certainly in the IOE Soft Straps region around `0xCAC`, but the exact dword and bit within that region has not been confirmed from a real firmware dump. Writing a guess to that region could corrupt the image, so we do not guess.

---

## HAP locations

| ME | Platform | HAP location | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| ME 12 LP | 8th/9th gen U (CNL/WHL/CFL) | PCHSTRP28 `fpsba+0x70` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 12 H | 8th/9th gen desktop (Z390/H370) | PCHSTRP32 `fpsba+0x80` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 13 | 10th gen Ice Lake LP | PCHSTRP28 `fpsba+0x70` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 14 | 10th gen Comet Lake LP | PCHSTRP28 `fpsba+0x70` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 15 LP | 11th gen Tiger Lake LP | PCHSTRP31 `fpsba+0x7C` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 15 H | 11th/12th gen TGL-H / RKL-H | PCHSTRP37 `fpsba+0x94` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 16 | 12th gen Alder Lake | PCHSTRP31 `fpsba+0x7C` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 16.1 | 13th gen Raptor Lake | PCHSTRP31 `fpsba+0x7C` bit 16 | Confirmed |
| ME 18 | 14th gen Meteor Lake | IOE Soft Straps ~`0xCAC` | Research — write skipped |

---

## How to help confirm the MTL offset

If you have a Meteor Lake machine and can get a before/after firmware diff, one dump is all it takes.

**Using Intel FIT (Windows):**

1. Dump your BIOS: `sudo flashrom -p internal -r stock.bin`
2. Open in Intel Flash Image Tool, enable HAP/AltMeDisable, save the output
3. Run `python3 hap_diff.py stock.bin fit_output.bin`
4. Open an issue with the output

**Using a BIOS toggle (if your BIOS exposes ME disable):**

1. `sudo flashrom -p internal -r before.bin`
2. Enable ME disable in BIOS, reboot
3. `sudo flashrom -p internal -r after.bin`
4. Run `python3 hap_diff.py before.bin after.bin`
5. Open an issue with the output

`hap_diff.py` filters out all the FIT noise and focuses on the IOE strap region specifically. If it finds a single-bit change at bit 16 it prints the exact offset and the code to add to me_cleaner.

---

## Usage

Same as main.

```
python3 me_cleaner_experimental.py -c your_dump.bin
python3 me_cleaner_experimental.py -s your_dump.bin -O patched.bin
```

